@page "/"

<PageTitle>LegacyBlazorJs Intro Site</PageTitle>

<section class="hero content-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">LegacyBlazorJs</p>
    <h1>Blazor Server for older browsers</h1>
    <p class="lead">
        LegacyBlazorJs rebuilds the official ASP.NET Core Blazor JavaScript runtime for multiple
        language targets, so a Blazor Server app can keep working on browsers that are no longer
        covered by modern evergreen support policies.
    </p>
    <p>
        This intro site itself loads the <code>blazor.server.es5.js</code> profile, so the <a href="#interactive">interactive examples</a>
        below are intended to remain usable even on Internet Explorer 11.
    </p>
    <p>
        Go interactive sample
    </p>
    <p>
        Please refer to the <a href="https://github.com/arika0093/LegacyBlazorJs">GitHub</a> for details.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="content-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Overview</p>
    <h2>What this project does</h2>
    <p>
        ASP.NET Core officially targets evergreen browsers. Starting with newer .NET releases, the
        built-in Blazor runtime also assumes more recent JavaScript features. This project rebuilds
        <code>blazor.web.js</code> and <code>blazor.server.js</code> into profiles ranging from ES5 to ES2022.
    </p>
    <p>
        The main goal is practical compatibility for enterprise environments where browser upgrades
        are slow or constrained. The primary focus is Blazor Server. WebAssembly is not supported.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="content-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Targets</p>
    <h2>Compatibility goals</h2>
    <ul class="simple-list">
        <li>Chrome 23 and later through the ES5 build.</li>
        <li>Internet Explorer 11, as far as the required platform APIs allow.</li>
        <li>Newer Chrome-based browsers through newer profile builds such as ES2015, ES2017, and ES2022.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        In environments without dynamic import support, some third-party libraries may still be limited.
        Even so, a minimal Blazor Server page can often be delivered successfully.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="content-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">How To Use</p>
    <h2>Install and replace the script</h2>
    <p>
        Install the NuGet package in your Blazor Web App, then replace the default framework script
        with the profile that matches your browser target.
    </p>
    <pre><code>dotnet add package LegacyBlazorJs</code></pre>
    <pre><code>&lt;script src="_content/LegacyBlazorJs/blazor.server.es2015.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>
    <p>
        If you do not need WebAssembly features, prefer <code>blazor.server.*.js</code>. It is smaller
        and is the recommended choice for legacy browser support.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="feature-grid" id="interactive">
    <article class="feature">
        <p class="eyebrow">Counter</p>
        <h2>Interactive counter</h2>
        <p class="counter-value" role="status" translate="no">
            @currentCount
        </p>
        <p>
            This counter is rendered through Blazor Server and is intended to keep working on older browsers too.
        </p>
        <div class="button-row">
            <button class="primary-action" @onclick="IncrementCount">Increment</button>
            <button class="ghost-action" @onclick="ResetCount">Reset</button>
        </div>
    </article>

    <article class="feature">
        <p class="eyebrow">Redirect</p>
        <h2>Interactive navigation</h2>
        <p>
            Client-side navigation via <code>NavigateTo</code> should also continue to work with the legacy profile.
        </p>
        <button class="secondary-action" @onclick="OpenRedirectDemo">Try Redirect</button>
    </article>
</section>

@inject NavigationManager Navigation
@code {
    private int currentCount;

    private void IncrementCount()
    {
        currentCount++;
    }

    private void ResetCount()
    {
        currentCount = 0;
    }

    private void OpenRedirectDemo()
    {
        Navigation.NavigateTo("/redirect-target");
    }
}
